cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.AI 

The paper deals with the task of retrieving clips within videos based on natural language queries, which involves cross-modal reasoning over multiple frames. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach that predicts the start and end frames by leveraging cross-modal interactions between text and video, which involves machine learning techniques such as recurrent networks and predictor networks. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
